Welcome! Our Camp has been present for over 30 years. Many Generations have enjoyed New Smyrna Beach RV Park and we look forward to including your family too!
New Smyrna Beach is 8 gorgeous miles of white sand on Florida’s east coast.
New Smyrna Beach RV Park and Campground
is 5 miles inland with over 200 sites, located just 15 minutes south of Daytona Beach in the peaceful small town charm of New Smyrna Beach.
Several events are growing in popularity each year, including Biketoberfest, Daytona 500 and Bike Week.
Our Woodall’s and Trailer Life Rated
New Smyrna Beach RV Park and Campground
is a popular spot each winter with Snowbirds and retirees. Many customers have made lifelong friendships and return each year.
The Air Conditioned Cabins are popular in the summer with local Central Floridians looking to take advantage of the cooler coastal weather.

Nestled between the Indian River Lagoon and 17 miles of white sand beaches, New Smyrna Beach is a haven for outdoor enthusiasts. Wet and dry trails pepper the area, making it prime for cycling, kayaking, and other sporting adventures. Beachside, you’ll find ample opportunities for fishing, surfing, and scuba diving. You can even go for a spin in the clouds in a vintage plane! Whether you want to dive deep or go sky high, you can make it happen in New Smyrna Beach.
ACTIVITIES & ADVENTURE
The charming town of New Smyrna Beach is full of laid-back vibes, but our variety of restaurants is off the hook, offering up some seriously mouthwatering big-city flavors.
TOP RESTAURANTS
The arts have a permanent home in New Smyrna Beach. The city has the distinction of being included in the book, “The 100 Best Small Art Towns in America: Where to Discover Creative Communities, Fresh Air, and Affordable Living” by John Villani.
ARTS & CULTURE
